Deputy President William Ruto has hosted President Uhuru Kenyatta and former Prime Minister Raila Odinga for lunch at his Karen residence.  President Uhuru Kenyatta and Deputy President William Ruto at Ruto's Karen residence. /COURTESY Details are still scanty but the Star understands that the three leaders discussed various issues affecting the country. President Uhuru was the first to arrive for the meeting followed by Raila 34 minutes later.  DP William Ruto, Raila Odinga, President Uhuru Kenyatta and Senator Kipchumba Murkomen at Ruto's Karen residence, November 2, 2018. /COURTESY Both Uhuru and Raila arrived in convoy but their aides and security officials were kept away from the meeting. It is the first time that Ruto is formally hosting Uhuru and Raila since the March 9 handle which reset the political relationship between the two.  President Uhuru Kenyatta and DP William Ruto. /COURTESY The three were also joined by Senate Majority Leader Kipchumba Murkomen. The leaders had earlier in the day attended the requiem mass of the late former Maendeleo ya Wanawake Organisation chairperson Jane Kiano at the St Francis ACK church, Karen. Click here for the latest political news   